Habitus (
Fig. 2E
) elongate, evenly convex and sublustrous; well pigmented: mostly blackish brown; mouthparts, apical half of ultimate antennomere, and tarsi somewhat paler. Dorsum continually clothed with short, recumbent and sallow pubescence; elytra intermixed with long, erect hairs.

